metadata.name: Alcyone #208
metadata.description:
And the ragged rock in the restless waters,
Waves wash over it, fogs conceal it;
On a halcyon day it is merely a monument,
In navigable weather it is always a seamark
To lay a course by: but in the sombre season
Or the sudden fury, is what it always was.

THE DRY SALVAGES

metadata.name: Coloring With Lines #195
metadata.description:
This project started as a way to teach myself more about classes in p5.js by trying to code the "Chaos Game" method of plotting a Serpinski Triangle

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kbKtFN71Lfs

Once figured out, I expanded the method to other shapes to see if different types of fractals might form. They did not, but the result was a series of points that could be connected with thin lines to draw shapes without using the native functions of p5. After working on colors it seemed like a nice enough project to release for free to everyone. Thank you all for your interest and support, hope you get a cool one!

metadata.name: Griddy #79
metadata.description:
《Griddy》started from a survey of Mondrian’s and Raven Kwok’s work. During the process, several primitive elements are put together to form 《Griddy》.

The palette is chosen from RYB, RGB, CMYK. Three possible thicknesses are chosen for the grid line, and with a possibility of the same color with the background, forming a “negative space” effect. Three ratios for the partition of space, and with a possibility of “inverted ratio” when dividing space. For filling the grid, three prime numbers will be randomly selected for each color. And finally, a possibility that the whole grid moves.

Coding with the lovely Pts.js.
